cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MA, cs.CV 

The paper focuses on developing a meta-learning algorithm for continuous adaptation in nonstationary and adversarial environments. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of a new multi-agent competitive environment, RoboSumo, and the design of iterated adaptation games suggest that the paper may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also mentions experiments with computer vision tasks, indicating that it may also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category.
